---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const baseTrim = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<Layout title="About — AI Tech Blog" description="About this blog and its author: an algorithm developer working on IMU sensor fusion and image processing.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">About</h1>
    <div class="prose max-w-none text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
      <h2>About This Blog</h2>
      <p>
        This blog is my personal study log. I write about the machine learning and
        engineering topics I am actively learning and using at work — PyTorch internals,
        GPU environments, model optimization for edge devices, and the practical side of
        working with large language models.
      </p>
      <p>
        Writing things down forces me to actually understand them. Publishing them keeps
        me honest: every article here is reviewed and fact-checked before it goes live,
        and I correct posts when I find mistakes.
      </p>

      <h2>About the Author</h2>
      <p>
        I write under the name <strong>B1ack</strong>. I work as an <strong>algorithm
        developer for IMU sensors and image processing</strong>. My day-to-day work
        involves sensor signal processing, computer vision pipelines, and deploying
        models to resource-constrained hardware — which is why topics like CUDA setup,
        pipeline profiling, and quantization show up often on this blog.
      </p>

      <h2>What You Will Find Here</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Deep learning framework internals and practical usage (PyTorch, JAX)</li>
        <li>GPU and development environment setup guides</li>
        <li>Model optimization for edge and embedded targets</li>
        <li>Notes on evaluating and integrating large language models</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        Found an error, or want to discuss a topic? See the
        <a href={`${baseTrim}/contact`}>contact page</a> — I read every message.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
